<LP>
   PASADENA, Calif. -- Jacobs Engineering Group Inc. said it
received a contract from Titanium Metals Corp., Henderson,
Nev., to provide engineering services for a vacuum-distilled
titanium sponge manufacturing facility.
   Terms weren't discosed. The project is scheduled to be
completed in December 1992. Advanced technology and financing
for the 22-million-pound annual capacity plant will be
provided by a group of Japanese companies including Toho
Titanium Co. and its primary shareholders: Nippon Mining Co.
and Mitsui &amp; Co. Titanium Metals is a unit of Houston-based
Baroid Corp.
