<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   TAIPEI -- Taiwan's indirect trade with China via Hong Kong
gained 4.6% to $1.83 billion during the first half of the
year from $1.75 billion a year earlier, the Board of Foreign
Trade reported.
   Taiwan's exports to China totaled $1.48 billion between
January and June, against $1.45 billion a year earlier.
Taiwan's imports from China climbed 18% to $349 million from
$295.7 million a year earlier.
</LP>
