   NEW YORK -- The New York Stock Exchange announced two new
listings, the American Stock Exchange added one, and the
National Market System of the over-the-counter market added
four.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Cash America Investments Inc., Fort Worth, Texas, an owner
and operator of pawnshops previously traded on the American
Stock Exchange, begins trading Friday on the Big Board with
the symbol PWN. Mexico Equity &amp; Income Fund Inc., New York, a
closed-end management investment company, started trading on
Wednesday as an initial public offering under the symbol MXE.
                                                                                                       

