company, began trading Wednesday, as GOIL.
                                                                                                       

   Lunar Corp., a Madison, Wis., maker of products for
diagnosing and treating metabolic bone diseases, began
trading Tuesday, under LUNR. Marcam Corp., a Newton, Mass.,
supplier of applications software for process manufacturers,
began trading Thursday, under MCAM.
                                                                                                       

   Southmark Corp., a Dallas real estate and financial
services firm, recently reorganized after bankruptcy
proceedings, and previously traded on the Big Board, began
trading Monday, on a when-issued basis under SMRKV for common
stock and SMRPV for preferred shares.
                                                                                                       

   Separately, the Pacific Stock Exchange began trading
options on Cracker Barrel Old Country Store Inc., owner and
operator of country store-theme restaurants, under CBRL.
