<HL>
   Treasury Will Raise
   $1.2 Billion New Cash
</HL>
<DATE>
08/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17
</SO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)
</IN>
<GV>
TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Treasury plans to raise $1.2 billion in
new cash Thursday by selling about $10.5 billion in 52-week
bills and redeeming $9.29 billion in maturing bills.
   The bills, which will be available in minimum
denominations of $10,000, will be dated Aug. 30 and will
mature Aug. 29, 1991.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Tenders for the bills must be received by 1 p.m. EDT
Thursday at the Treasury or at Federal Reserve banks or
branches.
